Before taking part in this study, please read the consent form below and click on the "I Agree" button at the bottom of the page if you understand the statements and freely consent to participate in the study: 

 

The purpose of this study is to examine your perceptions of employees. In this study, you will view hypothetical potential employees for a company and will provide your evaluations.  

 

Your participation in this research is entirely voluntary. Please answer the questions as best as you can, but feel free to skip any question that makes you uncomfortable. You will not lose any potential benefits if you skip questions that make you uncomfortable. You are free to discontinue participation at any time. 

 

You must be at least 18 years of age to participate in this research. By signing this form, you are providing your consent to participate in this research. There is no penalty for not participating. Participation for this study will take approximately 5 minutes of your time and you will receive $1.00 for your participation. There are no risks associated with this study beyond what you might encounter in daily life. 

 

All responses will be held in the strictest confidence. Only the researchers will have access to your individual responses. Your individual responses will not be shared with anyone else. Aggregated findings, collected across several different courses, will be used in any reports of the data. 

 

You can obtain a copy of a report describing the results of this research when it is completed or with any questions you may have by contacting Dr. Nicholas Salter (nicholas.p.salter@hofstra.edu). You may also contact the chair of the Hofstra IRB Committee (irb@hofstra.edu) if you have any questions or concerns about this research.
